owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate that the this implementation remains valid after an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.to: The beneficiary address to mint to.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

params.withdrawalIndex: The index in the array within `lockedDeposits`.

deposit(uint256,uint256,address).notice: Enables a deposit of $BTRST ERC20 to this contract on behalf of a beneficiary. The cumulative deposit is used off-chain to determine a user's level. A deposit is only successful if the beneficiary's wallet already contains a braintrust membership NFT. This function is ideally called by the beneficiary, but ultimately anyone who calls it should have enough $BTRST, and should have already approved this contract to spend it. Business Rule? A deposit will only succeed if a beneficiary already has a membership NFT.

getLockedDepositByIndex(address,uint256).notice: Returns the locked deposit for a given wallet at a given index.

getTotalLockedDepositAmount(address).notice: Returns the total locked deposits for a given wallet.NOTE: intented for off-chain.

getTotalLockedDepositByAddress(address).notice: Returns the total locked deposits for a given wallet.NOTE: intented for off-chain.

getTotalUnlockedDeposit(address).notice: Returns the total unlocked deposits for a given wallet.

lock(uint256,uint256,address,uint256).notice: Enables a locked deposit of $BTRST ERC20 to this contract on behalf of a beneficiary. A locked deposit is different from an ordinary deposit mainly because it is frozen on this contract until the available time has elapsed. The cumulative deposit is used off-chain to determine a user's level. A locked deposit is only successful if a beneficiary's wallet already contains a braintrust membership NFT.

lockedDeposits(address,uint256).notice: Keyed by beneficiary wallet address, the associated Profiles. Each call to lockDeposit() function will add a new item in the Profile[] array for the given beneficiary.

relayer().notice: The relayer. Is an EOA that holds ETH which is used to pay gas for certain method calls.e.g `safeMint()`.

safeMint(address).notice: Mints a new NFT to a specified address.

setBaseURI(string).notice: Changes the NFT base URL to a new value.

setRelayer(address).notice: Changes the relayer address to a new one.

unlockedDeposits(address).notice: Keyed by beneficiary wallet address, the associated Profile data.

withdrawLockedDeposit(uint256,uint256).notice: Enables a user to transfer their locked $BTRST deposit to their wallet. This is only possible if available time has elapsed.

withdrawUnlockedDeposit(uint256).notice: Enables a user to transfer their $BTRST deposit to their wallet.
